    • Method Detail

      • type

        <T,B extends BaseValue<T>> Key.Builder<T,B> type(TypeToken<B> token)
        Starter method for the builder, to be used immediately after Key.builder() is called. This defines the generics for the builder itself to provide the properly generified Key.

        Common TypeTokens can be found in TypeTokens. If a new TypeToken is to be created, it is recommended to create an anonymous class instance of a token, as recommended by Guava's wiki found here.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The element type of the Key
        B - The base value type of the key
        Parameters:
        token - The type token, preferably an anonymous
        Returns:
        This builder, generified
